"v.脱去；剥蚀；剥夺 【英】 v. 脱去，剥蚀，剥夺 (to make bare or naked) 【考】 反义词：cover(覆盖) 【记】 de+nude(=naked,赤裸 的)→完全赤裸→脱去 【同】 同根词：nudism(裸体 主义)；nudity(裸体) 【例】 He was denuded of all pride. v. 脱去; 剥蚀(因腐蚀而露出石层) 【记】de使得, nude = naked赤裸的一脱去 【参】nudism(n 裸体主义); nudity(n 裸体) 【反】cover(v 覆盖) 【记】de + nude 赤裸的→使完全赤裸 denude (v.)  early 15c. (implied in denuded), from Middle French dénuder, from Latin denudare ""to lay bare, strip; uncover, expose,"" from de- ""away"" (see de-) + nudare ""to strip,"" from nudus ""naked, bare"" (see naked). Related: Denuding."
